閉嘴  閉嘴
Shut up! Shut up!

333
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:51,328
我給你添麻煩了
I've caused you some trouble.

334
00:33:51,396 --> 00:33:52,624
不
No.

335
00:33:53,999 --> 00:33:56,160
母親...我母親
Mother... my mother...

336
00:33:56,868 --> 00:33:58,665
怎么說呢
What is the phrase?

337
00:33:59,605 --> 00:34:01,869
她今天心情不太好
She isn't quite herself today.

338
00:34:02,674 --> 00:34:06,633
你不必麻煩了  我真的不餓
You shouldn't have bothered. I really don't have that much of an appetite.

339
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,004
我很抱歉
Oh, I'm sorry.

340
00:34:12,651 --> 00:34:15,643
我希望能替她道歉
I wish you could apologize for other people.

341
00:34:16,288 --> 00:34:18,017
不要緊
Don't worry about it.

342
00:34:18,090 --> 00:34:21,651
不過既然你准備好了晚餐  我們一起吃吧
But as long as you've fixed a supper, we may as well eat it.

343
00:34:32,204 --> 00:34:36,732
服務台那里會比較暖和
It might be nicer and warmer in the office.

344
00:34:51,089 --> 00:34:52,886
雨停了
Well, it stopped raining.

345
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:55,449
服務台不太方便
Eating in an office is just too officious.

346
00:34:56,728 --> 00:34:58,286
后面有個小房間
I have the parlor back here.

347
00:34:58,363 --> 00:34:59,489
好的
All right.

348
00:35:15,047 --> 00:35:16,071
請坐
Sit down.

349
00:35:16,148 --> 00:35:17,775
謝謝
Thank you.

350
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:22,749
你真好
You're very kind.

351
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:27,114
都是你的  我不餓  你吃吧
It's all for you. I'm not hungry. Go ahead.

352
00:35:33,732 --> 00:35:35,893
你...你吃東西的樣子像只鳥
You... you eat like a bird.

353
00:35:37,469 --> 00:35:39,528
你很了解它們
And you'd know, of course.

354
00:35:40,238 --> 00:35:41,796
不  也不是
No, not really.

355
00:35:42,374 --> 00:35:45,275
總之  我聽說  跟鳥的吃相一樣
Anyway, I hear the expression ..eats like a bird..

356
00:35:45,344 --> 00:35:49,440
是不對...不對的
Is really a false... falsity.

357
00:35:50,349 --> 00:35:53,216
因為鳥的食量很大
Because birds really eat a tremendous lot.

358
00:35:56,054 --> 00:35:59,421
我對鳥的習性不是很了解
But I don't really know anything about birds.

359
00:35:59,491 --> 00:36:01,288
我喜歡收集東西
My hobby is stuffing things.

360
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:03,191
比如標本
You know, taxidermy.

361
00:36:04,029 --> 00:36:07,260
我想我比較喜歡鳥
And I guess I'd just rather stuff birds

362
00:36:07,866 --> 00:36:10,494
因為我討厭看到野獸做成的標本
Because I hate the look of beasts when they're stuffed.

363
00:36:10,569 --> 00:36:12,560
像狐狸和人猿什么的
You know, foxes and chimps.

364
00:36:12,637 --> 00:36:16,573
有些人甚至拿狗和貓做標本  我可做不到
Some people even stuff dogs and cats, but, oh, I can't do that.

365
00:36:17,175 --> 00:36:19,609
我想只有鳥類標本比較好看  因為...
I think only birds look well stuffed because...

366
00:36:19,678 --> 00:36:23,136
因為它們會和你培養出情感
Well, because they're kind of passive to begin with.

367
00:36:23,815 --> 00:36:26,579
很奇怪的愛好  很稀奇
It's a strange hobby. Curious.

368
00:36:27,319 --> 00:36:28,308
也很不尋常
Uncommon, too.

369
00:36:28,387 --> 00:36:30,048
我想也是
Oh, I imagine so.

370
00:36:30,689 --> 00:36:34,147
這并不如你想像的花錢  很便宜的
And it's not as expensive as you'd think. It's cheap, really.

371
00:36:34,226 --> 00:36:36,751
只要有針線  蘇打粉
You know, needles and thread, sawdust.

372
00:36:36,828 --> 00:36:39,592
只要花錢買些化學品就可以了
The chemicals are the only thing that cost anything.

373
00:36:39,664 --> 00:36:41,723
人應該有愛好的
A man should have a hobby.

374
00:36:42,434 --> 00:36:46,336
這...這不只是愛好
Well, it's... It's more than a hobby.

375
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:51,737
愛好是用來消磨時間  而不是充實自己的
A hobby's supposed to pass the time, not fill it.

376
00:36:52,544 --> 00:36:54,478
你感到空虛嗎
Is your time so empty?

377
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:55,638
不
No.

378
00:36:57,382 --> 00:36:59,646
我經營這家旅館
Well, I run the office

379
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:02,152
打掃房間
And tend the cabins and grounds

380
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:04,950
幫我母親做些
And do little errands for my mother.

381
00:37:05,023 --> 00:37:08,322
她認為我可以做的事
The ones she allows I might be capable of doing.

382
00:37:08,894 --> 00:37:11,021
你和朋友們出去嗎
Do you go out with friends?

383
00:37:13,999 --> 00:37:16,900
一個男孩最好的朋友就是他母親
Well, a boy's best friend is his mother.

384
00:37:19,204 --> 00:37:23,140
你一生中還從未有過空虛的時候吧
You've never had an empty moment in your entire life, have you?

385
00:37:25,177 --> 00:37:26,974
一個人的時候會有
Only my share.

386
00:37:27,045 --> 00:37:28,535
你要去哪里
Where are you going?

387
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:33,283
我不是要刺探你
I didn't mean to pry.

388
00:37:33,351 --> 00:37:35,376
我在找一處沒人去的地方
I'm looking for a private island.

389
00:37:37,155 --> 00:37:39,521
你在逃避什么事情嗎
What are you running away from?

390
00:37:42,027 --> 00:37:44,086
為什么這么問
Why do you ask that?

391
00:37:46,064 --> 00:37:48,658
人們總是在逃避事情
People never run away from anything.

392
00:37:51,403 --> 00:37:54,998
雨下的時間不長  你知道我怎么想的嗎
The rain didn't last long, did it? You know what I think?

393
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:57,832
我在想
I think that

394
00:38:00,045 --> 00:38:02,536
我們都掉在自己的陷阱中
We're all in our private traps,

395
00:38:03,248 --> 00:38:06,581
被它緊緊困住  沒人爬得出來
Clamped in them, and none of us can ever get out.

396
00:38:08,987 --> 00:38:11,182
我們想抓住什么東西
We scratch and claw,

397
00:38:11,990 --> 00:38:14,788
但抓到的只是空氣  只是陷阱
But only at the air, only at each other.

398
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:19,221
結果  沒有一點進展
And for all of it, we never budge an inch.

399
00:38:20,432 --> 00:38:23,629
有時候我們根本沒掉入那些陷阱
Sometimes we deliberately step into those traps.

400
00:38:25,971 --> 00:38:29,065
我掉進去了  我不在乎了
I was born in mine. I don't mind it anymore.

401
00:38:29,140 --> 00:38:31,836
你應該在乎  應該在乎的
Oh, but you should. You should mind it.

402
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:34,276
我在乎  但我想說不在乎
Oh, I do, but I say I don't.

403
00:38:37,349 --> 00:38:41,285
如果有人像你母親對你那樣
You know, if anyone ever talked to me the way I heard,

404
00:38:41,953 --> 00:38:44,114
同我說話的話...
The way she spoke to you...

405
00:38:46,024 --> 00:38:48,891
有時候當她那樣對我說話時
Sometimes when she talks to me like that,

406
00:38:49,494 --> 00:38:53,931
我真想上樓去咒罵她  永遠離開她
I feel I'd like to go up there and curse her and leave her forever.

407
00:38:54,633 --> 00:38:56,464
至少不會順從她
Or at least defy her.

408
00:39:01,106 --> 00:39:02,869
但我知道我不能這樣
But I know I can't.

409
00:39:04,609 --> 00:39:06,008
她病了
She's ill.

410
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,308
聽她說話的聲音很健康
She sounded strong.

411
00:39:09,447 --> 00:39:11,142
不  她病了
No, I mean ill.

412
00:39:13,418 --> 00:39:17,115
自從我父親死后她扶養我到現在
She had to raise me all by herself, after my father died.

413
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:20,783
當時我才5歲  對她的打擊很大
I was only five and it must've been quite a strain for her.

414
00:39:20,859 --> 00:39:23,293
她不必出去工作
I mean, she didn't have to go to work or anything like that.

415
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:25,488
他給她留下了一點兒錢
He left her a little money.

416
00:39:25,964 --> 00:39:29,866
几年前母親遇到了一個男人
Anyway, a few years ago, mother met this man.

417
00:39:30,435 --> 00:39:33,700
他說服她蓋了這棟旅館
And he talked her into building this motel.

418
00:39:33,772 --> 00:39:36,138
他可以說服她干任何事
He could have talked her into anything.

419
00:39:36,207 --> 00:39:40,473
當他也死后  對她的打擊更大
And when he died, too, it was just too great a shock for her.

420
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:43,813
他死的樣子...
And the way he died...

421
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:50,517
你吃飯時不應該說這些的
I guess it's nothing to talk about while you're eating.

422
00:39:50,589 --> 00:39:54,992
總之  那對她是一大重創  她什么都沒了
Anyway, it was just too great a loss for her. She had nothing left.

423
00:39:56,695 --> 00:39:58,162
至少還有你啊
Except you.

424
00:39:59,564 --> 00:40:02,624
兒子是替代不了愛人的
Well, a son is a poor substitute for a lover.

425
00:40:03,602 --> 00:40:05,467
你為什么不離開呢
Why don't you go away?

426
00:40:07,038 --> 00:40:09,302
像你一樣  去一個沒人的地方嗎
To a private island, like you?

427
00:40:12,877 --> 00:40:15,345
不  不是像我
No, not like me.

428
00:40:16,381 --> 00:40:19,475
我不能那樣  誰來照顧她呢
I couldn't do that. Who'd look after her?

429
00:40:21,052 --> 00:40:23,111
她會很寂寞的
She'd be alone up there.

430
00:40:24,022 --> 00:40:25,922
壁爐的火會滅的
Her fire would go out.

431
00:40:26,691 --> 00:40:29,182
這里會寒冷得像座墳墓
It'd be cold and damp like a grave.

432
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:32,525
如果你愛某人
If you love someone,

433
00:40:32,597 --> 00:40:35,828
即使你恨他  你也不會這樣做
You don't do that to them, even if you hate them.

434
00:40:36,835 --> 00:40:39,395
你知道嗎  我不恨她
You understand, I don't hate her.

435
00:40:41,272 --> 00:40:43,297
我只是恨她變成這個樣子
I hate what she's become.

436
00:40:44,309 --> 00:40:46,106
我恨她的病態
I hate the illness.

437
00:40:47,545 --> 00:40:50,241
如果你把她安置在某處...
Wouldn't it be better if you put her

438
00:40:51,950 --> 00:40:53,542
是不是比較好
Someplace...

439
00:40:56,821 --> 00:40:59,915
你是說那個地方?  瘋人院?
You mean an institution? A madhouse?

440
00:41:04,062 --> 00:41:07,554
人們說的某處就是瘋人院  不是嗎
People always call a madhouse someplace, don't they?

441
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:09,691
把她安置在某處
Put her in someplace.

442
00:41:11,202 --> 00:41:14,262
抱歉  我不是說不照顧她
I'm sorry. I didn't mean it to sound uncaring.

443
00:41:15,173 --> 00:41:17,607
你對照顧知道多少
What do you know about caring?

444
00:41:17,676 --> 00:41:20,839
你到那種地方去看過嗎
Have you ever seen the inside of one of those places?

445
00:41:20,912 --> 00:41:23,142
他們又哭又笑
The laughing and the tears

446
00:41:23,915 --> 00:41:26,713
用陰冷的雙眼觀察你
And the cruel eyes studying you.

447
00:41:26,785 --> 00:41:28,480
我的母親去那種地方?
My mother there?

448
00:41:30,689 --> 00:41:32,554
但她不會傷害別人
But she's harmless.

449
00:41:35,193 --> 00:41:38,424
她不會傷害別人  就像那些標本鳥一樣
She's as harmless as one of those stuffed birds.

450
00:41:39,564 --> 00:41:40,929
對不起
I am sorry.

451
00:41:41,766 --> 00:41:45,702
我只是覺得...她好像在傷害你
I only felt... It seems she's hurting you.

452
00:41:47,372 --> 00:41:48,896
我沒有惡意
I meant well.

453
00:41:48,973 --> 00:41:50,668
人們總說沒有惡意
People always mean well.

454
00:41:51,576 --> 00:41:53,874
他們言辭溫和  動作優雅
They cluck their thick tongues and shake their heads

455
00:41:53,945 --> 00:41:56,573
建議正確  好像很優美一樣
And suggest, oh, so very delicately.

456
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:06,616
當然  我自己也對自己建議過
Of course, I've suggested it myself.

457
00:42:08,259 --> 00:42:10,727
但我討厭這種想法
But I hate to even think about it.

458
00:42:11,496 --> 00:42:12,986
她需要我
She needs me.

459
00:42:17,202 --> 00:42:19,397
她并不是...
It's not as if she were

460
00:42:19,471 --> 00:42:22,235
瘋子或者精神錯亂的人
A maniac, a raving thing.

461
00:42:24,776 --> 00:42:27,677
只是有時候會神智不清
She just goes a little mad sometimes.

462
00:42:30,749 --> 00:42:33,183
我們有時候也會神智不清
We all go a little mad sometimes.

463
00:42:35,887 --> 00:42:37,320
你沒有過嗎
Haven't you?

464
00:42:39,424 --> 00:42:40,516
有過
Yes.

465
00:42:41,693 --> 00:42:44,526
但一次就夠了
Sometimes just one time can be enough.

466
00:42:46,297 --> 00:42:47,662
謝謝你
Thank you.

467
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:50,827
謝謝你  諾曼
Thank you, Norman.

468
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:52,130
諾曼
Norman.

469
00:42:53,438 --> 00:42:57,272
你是不是要回房去了
Oh, you're not going back to your room already?

470
00:42:57,776 --> 00:42:59,243
我很累
I'm very tired.

471
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:03,178
明天還要開車  回鳳凰城
And I have a long drive tomorrow, all the way back to Phoenix.

472
00:43:03,548 --> 00:43:04,810
是嗎
Really?

473
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:08,685
我在那里闖了點禍
I stepped into a private trap back there

474
00:43:09,387 --> 00:43:13,118
我要回去處理一下
And I'd like to go back and try to pull myself out of it

475
00:43:14,926 --> 00:43:16,450
乘還來得及
Before it's too late for me, too.

476
00:43:16,528 --> 00:43:19,326
你真的不想再多待一會兒嗎
Are you sure you wouldn't like to stay just a little while longer?

477
00:43:19,397 --> 00:43:21,297
只是聊聊天
Just for talk?

478
00:43:21,766 --> 00:43:23,597
我很想  但是...
Oh, I'd like to, but...

479
00:43:23,668 --> 00:43:24,965
好吧
All right.

480
00:43:25,036 --> 00:43:26,755
那明天早晨再見
Well, I'll see you in the morning.

481
00:43:26,755 --> 00:43:28,665
我會給你帶點兒早點  好嗎
I'll bring you some breakfast, all right?

482
00:43:28,740 --> 00:43:29,968
什么時候走
What time?

483
00:43:30,041 --> 00:43:31,406
很早  黎明吧
Very early. Dawn.

484
00:43:32,110 --> 00:43:33,577
好  怎么稱呼...
All right, miss...

485
00:43:33,645 --> 00:43:34,771
克蘭
Crane.

486
00:43:34,846 --> 00:43:35,938
克蘭  沒錯
Crane. That's it.

487
00:43:36,014 --> 00:43:37,481
晚安
Good night.

488
00:47:45,129 --> 00:47:46,357
不
No!

489
00:47:48,933 --> 00:47:50,025
不
No!

490
00:49:52,924 --> 00:49:55,290
母親  天哪  母親
Mother! Oh, god, mother!

491
00:49:55,359 --> 00:49:57,224
血  血
Blood! Blood!

492
01:00:25,022 --> 01:00:26,956
我試過很多牌子
I've tried many brands.

493
01:00:27,591 --> 01:00:31,618
到目前為止  我用過的似乎都沒什么效果
So far, of those I've used, I haven't had much luck with any of them.

494
01:00:31,695 --> 01:00:34,061
看看這個牌子怎么說
Let's see what they say about this one.

495
01:00:34,131 --> 01:00:36,429
它說的那些成分
They tell you what its ingredients are

496
01:00:36,500 --> 01:00:40,527
保証可以驅除所有蚊虫
And how it's guaranteed to exterminate every insect in the world,

497
01:00:41,071 --> 01:00:43,665
但它沒說是不是有痛苦
But they do not tell you whether or not it's painless.

498
01:00:43,740 --> 01:00:47,471
我想  昆虫和人一樣  希望沒有痛苦地死去
And I say, insect or man, death should always be painless.

499
01:00:48,278 --> 01:00:50,542
我想這個牌子的品質
I suppose, this one seems to claim more and better

500
01:00:50,614 --> 01:00:53,447
應該比其他的好
Qualities than lots of the others.

501
01:01:04,328 --> 01:01:05,488
薩姆?
Sam?

502
01:01:05,963 --> 01:01:08,488
薩姆  有位女士找你
Sam! Lady wants to see you.

503
01:01:14,771 --> 01:01:15,760
小姐  什么事
Yes, miss?

504
01:01:15,839 --> 01:01:17,329
我是曼璐的姐姐
I'm Marion's sister.

505
01:01:17,808 --> 01:01:18,968
是萊拉呀
Oh, sure. Lila.

506
01:01:19,042 --> 01:01:20,304
曼璐在這里嗎
Is Marion here?

507
01:01:22,012 --> 01:01:23,445
當然不在
Well, of course not.

508
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:25,242
有什么事嗎
Something wrong?

509
01:01:28,518 --> 01:01:30,315
她星期五離開家
She left home on Friday.

510
01:01:30,387 --> 01:01:34,050
我和孩子在圖森度周末  那時我就沒見到她
I was in Tucson over the weekend and I haven't heard from her since.

511
01:01:34,124 --> 01:01:36,024
甚至沒接到她的電話
Not even a phone call.

512
01:01:36,660 --> 01:01:38,882
如果你們兩個要在一起  我不會管
Look, if you two are in this thing together, I don't care,

